# Versioning Rule (SonyBudControl)

See also the **global** rule at `~/.cursor/rules/android-versioning.mdc`.

## Current version
- `versionCode`: check `app/build.gradle.kts` defaultConfig
- `versionName`: must match the git tag (without the `v` prefix)

## Release process
1. `git tag --sort=-v:refname | head -1` — find latest tag
2. Bump `versionCode` (+1) and `versionName` in `app/build.gradle.kts`
3. Commit: `git commit -am "Bump to vX.Y.Z"`
4. Tag: `git tag vX.Y.Z`
5. Push both: `git push origin master && git push origin vX.Y.Z`
6. CI builds the APK and creates the GitHub release automatically

## Signing
The signing keystore (`app/budcontrol.keystore`) is committed to the repo so every CI build produces an APK with the same signature. Users can install updates without uninstalling.
